('The Little Prince', 'ntoine de Saint-ExupÃ©ry', 'The Little Prince is a timeless tale of a princeâ€™s journey from planet to planet in search of adventure. What he finds, however, are interactions with adults who leave him frustrated or dismayed. In the Sahara Desert, he runs into the bookâ€™s narrator, and the two start an eight-day journey filled with lessons. Donâ€™t let this bookâ€™s size fool youâ€”itâ€™s one of the most compelling short books weâ€™ve ever read. Itâ€™s also one of the most widely read classics all over the world. Whether you prefer reading in English, French, or another language, youâ€™re bound to find a copy.', 'Reynal & Hitchcock', '', '', '', '', '', '', '1', '', '', '', '', 1943, 96, '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fEPqgSNLfK8', 'the-little-prince.jpeg', 6),
('The Fellowship of the Ring', 'J.R.R. Tolkien', 'In The Fellowship of the Ring, the first book in the Lord of the Rings trilogy, journey to Middle-earth and into the world of Frodo Baggins, Samwise Gamgee, Gandalf the Grey, the dark lord Sauron, and the entire assemblage of Tolkienâ€™s most famous characters and story lines. Frodo is tasked with destroying the One Ring, the most powerful Ring in Mordor, but along the way, his quest is filled with many of Tolkienâ€™s unique and captivating characters, as well as an adventure of epic proportions. Though the world of Middle-earth is entirely made up, the trilogy teases out universal themes of good versus evil that have resonated with readers of all ages and backgrounds. Itâ€™s widely regarded as one of the best fantasy books of all time and a must-read for lovers of the genre.', 'George Allen & Unwin', '', '1', '', '', '', '', '1', '', '', '', '', 1954, 423, '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V75dMMIW2B4', 'the-fellowship-of-the-ring.jpeg', 7),
('The Handmaid\'s Tale', 'Margaret Atwood', 'Offred, a handmaid in the Republic of Gilead, has been removed from the home, family, and life that she knew only to be forced into service as a housemaidâ€”and a working pair of ovaries. As the population of Gilead falls, a womanâ€™s value becomes contingent upon her fertility and ability to reproduce, and those who can procreate are stripped of their independence. Margaret Atwoodâ€™s The Handmaidâ€™s Tale is one part cautionary tale and one part enthralling narrative. Though written decades ago, it remains chillingly compelling for our time as was proven by audience reactions to itâ€™s on-screen adaptation. While Season 6 of The Handmaidâ€™s tale is yet to be released, you can binge the rest of the show on Hulu if you like both watching and reading. Thereâ€™s a reason Readerâ€™s Digest counts it among the best feminist books.', 'McClelland and Stewart Houghton Mifflin Harcourt', '', '1', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 1985, 311, '', 'https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dVLiDETfx1c', 'the-handmaids-tale.jpeg', 8),
